          About the Job
             Our client is a Global Financial Services firm in NYC, they are looking for a VP level Lead Data Scientist.
             Lead Data Scientist within our Human Resources department.  Please see the description below and let me know if this is something you think you could fill?
             We are looking for a dynamic and results-driven Lead Data Scientist with 7+ years of experience to join the HR Business Intelligence & Advanced Analytics team.  This individual will be
             responsible for providing a strong data modeling capability to the Human Resources Department.
             The Business Intelligence & Advanced Analytics team supports HR and the Firm in the management of HR data and reporting, and in the continued development of strategy through insights derived from data analysis.  The team provides technical expertise, advice and support to a variety of crucial Firmwide processes related to recruitment, diversity, retention, advancement and development.
             The Lead Data Scientist Lead will work closely with the Business Intelligence team and with clients to develop and define opportunities and risks.  This person will work on delivering actionable insights and predictive models to help answer business questions around organizational and employee performance. Through application of advanced analytics and visualization, this person will identify insights and aid in the development of compelling story-telling to make strategic recommendations to senior HR management.
             Duties
             • Develop recommendations that inform business and HR decision-making
             • Consult with HR and business leaders to identify business problems, risks and opportunities
             • Offer actionable analysis and reporting to managers and executives, and interface with HR and other business functions
             • Define appropriate approaches and solve problems through rigorous analytic techniques that may include machine learning, text mining, process mining, network analysis, and data visualization
             • Develop clear and compelling storylines, accompanying visualizations, and recommendations
             • Apply new methodologies in the intersection of applied machine learning, computer science and statistics and make approximations where needed to build scalable algorithms
             Required Technical and Professional Expertise:
             • MS/PhD degree in Statistics, Computer Science, or related field
             • Demonstrated proficiency in computational tools such as Python, R, SPSS, SQL and a strong understanding of applied statistics theory
             • Passion for empirical research and developing data-driven solutions to difficult business questions
             • Ability to translate unstructured business problems into an abstract mathematical framework
             • Skills in or familiarity with data cleaning, natural language processing, machine learning, artificial intelligence, visualization, network analysis, and distributed computing are a plus
             • Familiarity with database concepts and structures
             • Effective at communicating to leaders at all levels, including the ability to convey complex quantitative analyses clearly
             • Strong project management skills
             • Ability to work in a fast paced environment with competing priorities
             • 7-10  years professional experience, with some experience in financial services or similar industry
             • Preferred: prior management experience,  experience with HR data and/or knowledge of Human Resources processes and principles
